deck: The magazine that features the Winx Club!
description:
Winx Club Magazine is based on popular Italian animated series Winx Club. Besides the comics, the magazine has articles written by Winx Club members: Winx Fashion written by Stella, Tecno Zone written by Tecna, Sound of Nature written by Flora, Magic Music written by Musa, Dance... Sport... and Fun! written by Aisha, Bloom's diary Il Diario di Bloom and a segment by her called Winx Time. There are also quizzes, horoscopes, Mondo Trix - article written by the Trix, sections Movies and Books, La Posta del Cuore (containing received love letters) and Mail and Sms, an interview with a celebrity and previews of Winx movies, animated series, merchandise and events. 
 
Winx Club Magazine is one of the most popular teen magazines published in Italy. Every month 120000 copies of it are printed, and about 80% are sold.
name: Winx Club Magazine

description:
Arsenic Lullaby was an ongoing anthology comic published by its writer/artist Douglas Pazkiewicz. Often praised for its dark humor, the series would be nominated for both a Harvey and Eisner award and even be picked by Wizard Magazine as the "On the Edge Pick of the Month".

Publishers

  • #01-14: A Silent Comics Inc
  • #15-17: AAA Milwaukee

The series would see a change in publishers near the end of its run, although the first twelve issues were published at a fairly steady rate, the thirteenth and fourteenth came out a lot slower and the latter of the two was originally solicited as the final issue of the series. Arsenic Lullaby's humor (and characters) would live on in a few spin-offs before the series returned (with a new publisher) and lasted another three issues before ending after a seventeen issue run.

Spin-Offs

Arsenic Lullaby has had several spin-offs through its run, some carrying its name while others had more unique names.

  • Arsenic Lullaby Christmas Special #1
  • Arsenic Lullabies #1-2
  • Laughter of the Damned #1-3
  • The Thousand Deaths of Baron Von Donut #1

Collections

Arsenic Lullaby has also been collected in various trades/hardcovers, the newer ones tending to make the older obsolete, as such they have been listed by order of current relevance.

  • #01-17: The Devil's Decade
  • #01-11: Year of the Fetus
  • #12-17: Donut Cometh
  • #01-14: The Devil's Hat Trick
  • #01-06: The Devil Your Neighbor
name: Arsenic Lullaby

description:
Original English-Language (OEL) manga.

For nearly a millennium, undead creatures have blended into a Europe driven by religious dogma...

Ein Delalune is an underground goth metal sensation on the Paris music scene. Tragic and beautiful, he has the edge on other goth music powerhouses... he's undead. But his newfound fame might just bring out the very phantoms of his past from whom he has been hiding for centuries, including his powerful brother, Leroux, and if the two don't reconcile, the entire undead nation could rise up from the depths of modern society to lay waste to mankind.
name: A Midnight Opera
